<HEAD>Dollar Mixed In Moribund Pre-Christmas Trading, Gold Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. dollar was mixed in moribund pre-Christmas
trading this morning. Gold prices were fractionally higher.
   ``Activity is very, very modest,'' said a Rome bank trader.
``There's absolutely no trend to be detected in the market.''
   In Frankfurt, a dealer at a major European bank said: ``Whatever
little activity we see comes from corporate desks.''
   Traders said the market is likely to remain trendless throughout
next week with business not picking up until the new year.
