<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Child's Body,0183</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Girl's Body Found Encased In Concrete</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WAYCROSS, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The body of a 3-year-old girl was found
encased in concrete and dumped along a dirt road in southeast
Georgia, but her identity remains a mystery.
   An autopsy Thursday at the State Crime Lab showed the child had
been dead one to two months when she was found Wednesday by a
curious timber worker in woods about 35 miles north of the Florida
border, said Sheriff Herbert E. Bond.
   Pathologists were continuing work today to determine the cause of
death.
   ``They were able to tell us she had not been shot or stabbed,''
Bond said.
   The child had been wrapped in a blanket and stuffed inside a gym
bag, which was then placed in a suitcase. The suitcase was sealed
with concrete, and placed in an abandoned TV console.
   The timber worker found the body when he spotted the suitcase and
opened it out of curiosity, police said.
   There are no small children who are known to be missing in the
area, Bond said.
</TEXT>
