<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BRF--BarberSlaying     12-23 0161</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Barber Slaying,0163</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Suspect Arrested in Barber's Slaying</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police have arrested a suspect in the slaying of a
barber who was shot to death by a customer upset over his haircut.
   Paul Williams, 34, of Aurora, was picked up Wednesday night in
the investigation into the death of Bobbie D. Willis, said Detective
John Wyckoff. No charges were immediately filed.
   Willis, 47, was killed Saturday at his Barber Bob's Barber Shop
by a man who was angry about the haircut the barber gave him.
   The man refused to pay and grew so angry that police were
summoned to the barber shop. The man paid $9 and left, but returned
with a pistol and opened fire on Willis as he was calling police for
help, authorities and witnesses said.
   Police had said the gunman was slender, in his 20s with very
short hair and a 3-inch, crescent-shape scar on the back of his
head. Williams matched that description.
</TEXT>
