<HEAD>Man Killed While He Was Showing His Girlfriend How To Defend
Herself</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man teaching his girlfriend how to
defend herself was killed when she shot him in the face as he
pretended to be a burglar in their home, police said.
   Frederick Williams, 26, was killed Thursday by a 12-gauge shotgun
blast at close range as he was teaching Yolanda Edwards, Duval
County Sheriff's spokesman Asa Higgs said.
   The couple had been discussing how Ms. Edwards, 21, could protect
herself from intruders, and Williams gave her the shotgun to use in
practice, deputies said. Williams apparently had loaded the gun and
disengaged a safety.
   Ms. Edwards, however, told police she thought her boyfriend had
unloaded the gun before handing it to her.
   After giving her the gun, Williams left the room and returned
posing as an intruder, police said. Ms. Edwards pointed the shotgun
at Williams and lightly squeezed the trigger, causing the gun to
discharge.
   Ms. Edwards then phoned police to report the shooting.
   Detectives who were called to the home concluded that the
shooting was accidental, Higgs said. No charges were filed against
Ms. Edwards.
