<NOTE>Eds: Debe is cq.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>COOKEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Heavy fog caused a pileup of as many as
30 vehicles this morning, killing one person and injuring more than
a dozen, officials said.
   It ``was like a chain reaction,'' said Highway Patrol Lt. Waymon
Cooper. The 8:45 a.m. crash occurred on Interstate 40 about four
miles west of here.
   ``We feel like there is a total of approximately 15 victims and
we only have one fatality so far,'' said Debe West, a spokeswoman at
Cookeville General Hospital. At least two or three people were
seriously injured.
   A trooper on the scene reported a pileup of possibly 25 to 30
vehicles, Cooper said.
   ``He's having trouble seeing,'' he said.
