<TEXT>
   Stock prices finished a half-day, pre-holiday
session firmer Friday, boosted by a recovery in monthly British
trade figures.
   But traders cautioned that the market was too thin to draw
meaningful conclusions about the data.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index finished 5.3
