<HEAD>American Brands Stock Shoots Up On Unilever Takeover Rumor</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   American Brands Inc.'s stock price was up 17
percent on the New York Stock Exchange today on rumors of a takeover
by Unilever, the British-Dutch consumer products conglomerate.
   Both companies declined to comment on the rumors, citing policies
against commenting on speculation.
   American Brands stock was up $9.87{ at $67.50 a share as of early
afternoon on Wall Street. At one point it had traded as high as
$70.25 a share, a 22 percent advance over Thursday's close.
   American Brands, based in Old Greenwich, Conn., makes tobacco and
liquor products as well as an assortment of golf balls, shoes and
office supplies.
   Unilever is mainly in the businesses of food and specialty
chemicals.
</TEXT>
