<FILEID>AP-NR-12-23-88 1519EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f AM-FortuneFinancial     12-23 0196</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Fortune Financial,0206</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Baldwin Securities Unit Makes Offer For Fortune Financial</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Baldwin Securities Corp. said Friday it offered
to buy Fortune Financial Group Inc., a Florida savings and loan
holding company, for about $180 million.
   The $33-a-share offer by the New York investment firm includes
$27 in cash and $6 in senior preferred stock. It is conditioned upon
acceptance by Fortune's board of directors.
   The Baldwin offer is the third Fortune Financial has received
from a company or person with close ties to Singer Co., the defense
contractor that financier Paul A. Bilzerian took private about a
year ago.
   A federal grand jury indicted Bilzerian on fraud charges
Wednesday in connection with four unsuccessful takeover attempts,
none of which involved Fortune Financial.
   Baldwin Chairman Arthur G. Cohenis is a Singer director. Offers
for Fortune have been made in the past few months _ and later
withdrawn _ from Bilzerian, Singer's chairman, and Alex Spanos,
another Singer director.
   Also vying for the Clearwater, Fla.-based Fortune Financial is
the New York investment firm Dyson-Kissner-Moran Corp., which on
Wednesday disclosed a $170 million offer, which includes $27 in cash
and $4 in preferred stock.
</TEXT>
